import React from "react";
import { Navbar, Nav, NavDropdown, Form, FormControl, Button } from 'react-bootstrap';

const MyNavbar = () => {
  return (
    <Navbar bg="light" expand="lg">
      <Navbar.Brand href="https://www.google.com/">Navbar</Navbar.Brand>
      <Navbar.Toggle aria-controls="basic-navbar-nav" />
      <Navbar.Collapse id="basic-navbar-nav">
        <Nav className="mr-auto">
          <Nav.Link href="https://www.google.com/" className="active" style={{ color: "black" }}>
            Home
          </Nav.Link>
          <Nav.Link href="https://www.google.com/" style={{ color: "black" }}>
            Link
          </Nav.Link>
          <NavDropdown title="Dropdown" style={{ color: "black" }}>
            <NavDropdown.Item href="https://www.google.com/">Action</NavDropdown.Item>
            <NavDropdown.Item href="https://www.google.com/">Another action</NavDropdown.Item>
            <NavDropdown.Divider />
            <NavDropdown.Item href="https://www.google.com/">Something else here</NavDropdown.Item>
          </NavDropdown>
          <Nav.Link href="https://www.google.com/" disabled style={{ color: "black" }}>
            Disabled
          </Nav.Link>
        </Nav>
        <Form className="d-flex">
          <FormControl type="text" placeholder="Search" className="mr-sm-2" />
          <Button variant="outline-success">Search</Button>
        </Form>
      </Navbar.Collapse>
    </Navbar>
  );
};

export default MyNavbar;
